ances of this class"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"directly. Instead, you retrieve an existing "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNUserLocation","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" object from the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"code":"userLocation","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" property of the map view displayed in your application."}],"fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNUserLocation"}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNUserLocation","title":"MLNUserLocation","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnuserlocation","kind":"symbol","type":"topic"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNShape":{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNShape","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNShape"}],"abstract":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNShape"},{"type":"text","text":" is an abstract class that represents a shape or annotation. Shapes"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"constitute the content of a map — not only the overlays atop the map, but also"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the content that forms the base map."}],"kind":"symbol","type":"topic","title":"MLNShape","role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnshape"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNShapeSource":{"abstract":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNShapeSource"},{"type":"text","text":" is a map content source that supplies vector shapes to be"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"shown on the map. The shapes may be instances of "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNShape"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNShape","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"or they may be defined by local or external"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"GeoJSON"},{"type":"text","text":" code. A shape source is added to an"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNStyle","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" object along with an "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNStyle","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" object. The vector style"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"layer defines the appearance of any content supplied by the shape source. You"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"can update a shape source by setting its "},{"code":"shape","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" or "},{"code":"URL","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" property."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNShapeSource","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","title":"MLNShapeSource","fragments":[{"text":"MLNShapeSource","kind":"identifier"}],"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnshapesource"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNVectorTileSource":{"title":"MLNVectorTileSource","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNVectorTileSource","type":"topic","abstract":[{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNVectorTileSource","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" is a map content source that supplies tiled vector data"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"in "},{"type":"text","text":"Mapbox Vector Tile"},{"type":"text","text":" format"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"to be shown on the map. The location of and metadata about the tiles are"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"defined either by an option dictionary or by an external file that conforms to"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"TileJSON specification"},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"A vector tile source is added to an "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNStyle","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" object along with one or more"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNVectorStyleLayer","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" objects. A vector style layer defines the appearance of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"any content supplied by the vector tile source."}],"fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNVectorTileSource"}],"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnvectortilesource"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNOverlay":{"url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnoverlay","type":"topic","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"MLNOverlay"}],"title":"MLNOverlay","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNOverlay"},{"type":"text","text":" protocol defines a specific type of annotation that represents"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"both a point and an area on a map. Overlay objects are essentially data objects"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that contain the geographic data needed to represent the map area. Overlays can"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"take the form of a polyline or polygon."}]},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibr